Cooked in my soup maker too so very easy to make and all items I regularly have to hand. Would also try adding more beans to make more substantial. Stirred through spinach in mine as I had some in the fridge that needed using up - delicious. This will become a regular in my house.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1036446"><a id="comment-1036446"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">cjhall</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 17th Jan, 2018</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">5.05</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="on"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Really smooth but properly filling soup. Also used a whole can of chickpeas - half before blending and half after. Will be lovely with a bit of naan bread or similar to dip in as well.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1033321"><a id="comment-1033321"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> 